<paragraph blockId="16.[136,1452,158,581]" pageId="16" pageNumber="169">
C 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[208,438,158,184]" pageId="16" pageNumber="169">onservation Status:</emphasis>
<emphasis box="[438,698,158,184]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="169">
— 
<taxonomicName box="[467,698,158,184]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Bertolonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="16" pageNumber="169" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="igrapiuna">Bertolonia igrapiuna</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
has an EOO of 
<quantity box="[872,942,158,187]" metricMagnitude="4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.8" pageId="16" pageNumber="169" unit="km" value="28.0">28 km</quantity>
² and AOO of 
<quantity box="[1096,1168,158,187]" metricMagnitude="4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.6" pageId="16" pageNumber="169" unit="km" value="16.0">16 km</quantity>
², and should be classified as “Critically Endangered” (CR), following 
<bibRefCitation author="IUCN Standards and Petitions Subcommittee &amp; Cambridge, UK" box="[652,806,194,220]" pageId="16" pageNumber="169" refId="ref19879" refString="IUCN Standards and Petitions Subcommittee (2017) Guidelines for Using the IUCN Red List Categories and Criteria. Version 13 (March 2017). Prepared by the IUCN species survival commission. IUCN Council, Gland, Switzerland and Cambridge, UK, 108 pp. Available from: http: // cmsdocs. s 3. amazonaws. com / RedList Guidelines. pdf (Accessed 9 February 2019)" type="book" year="2017">IUCN (2017)</bibRefCitation>
categories. This species has been found exclusively in “Parque Nacional Serra das Lontras”.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="16.[136,1452,158,581]" pageId="16" pageNumber="169">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,265,266,292]" pageId="16" pageNumber="169">Notes:</emphasis>
— 
<taxonomicName box="[294,533,266,292]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Bertolonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="16" pageNumber="169" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="igrapiuna">
<emphasis box="[294,533,266,292]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="169">Bertolonia igrapiuna</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is endemic to 
<collectingRegion box="[706,774,266,292]" country="Brazil" name="Bahia" pageId="16" pageNumber="169">Bahia</collectingRegion>
, occurring in montane rainforests (
<figureCitation box="[1177,1262,266,292]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[136,229,1949,1971]" captionTargetBox="[341,1239,654,1912]" captionTargetId="figure-255@5.[340,1247,641,1924]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Distributions of species of Bertolonia in Bahia.A. Bertolonia alternifolia. B. Bertolonia angustipetala. C. Bertolonia bullata. D. Bertolonia carmoi. E. Bertolonia cuspidata. F. Bertolonia hirsutissima. G. Bertolonia igrapiuna. H. Bertolonia kollmannii." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6597686" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6597686/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="169">
Fig. 
<quantity box="[1231,1262,266,292]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="kg" metricValue="3.0" pageId="16" pageNumber="169" unit="g" value="3.0">3g</quantity>
</figureCitation>
). Collected with flowers from November to March, and fruits from December to June. The species is characterized by the branches, petioles and leaf blades only glandulose-punctate, by the elliptic or ovate leaf blades with shortly attenuate, obtuse or occasionally asymmetric base, and anthers dehiscing through an extrorse pore. It is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="(Bonpland 1823: 144) De Candolle (1828: 113)" authorityName="De Candolle" authorityPageNumber="113" authorityYear="1828" baseAuthorityName="Bonpland" baseAuthorityPageNumber="144" baseAuthorityYear="1823" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Bertolonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="16" pageNumber="169" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="leuzeana">
<emphasis box="[1194,1326,374,400]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="169">B. leuzeana</emphasis>
(Bonpland 1823: 144) 
<bibRefCitation author="De Candolle, A. P." box="[265,545,410,437]" pageId="16" pageNumber="169" pagination="99 - 202" refId="ref19166" refString="De Candolle, A. P. (1828) Melastomataceae. In: Prodromus systematis naturalis regni vegetabilis 3. Sumptibus Sociorum Treuttel &amp; Wurtz, Paris, pp. 99 - 202." type="book chapter" year="1828">De Candolle (1828: 113)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, from the state of 
<collectingRegion box="[746,911,410,436]" country="Brazil" name="Rio de Janeiro" pageId="16" pageNumber="169">Rio de Janeiro</collectingRegion>
. Both have flat, ovate or elliptic leaf blades with non-cordate bases (attenuate or obtuse in 
<taxonomicName box="[612,755,447,472]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Bertolonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="16" pageNumber="169" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="igrapiuna">
<emphasis box="[612,755,447,472]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="169">B. igrapiuna</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, acute in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="De Candolle" authorityYear="1828" baseAuthorityName="Bonpland" baseAuthorityYear="1823" box="[870,1003,446,472]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Bertolonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="16" pageNumber="169" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="leuzeana">
<emphasis box="[870,1003,446,472]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="169">B. leuzeana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and sparse ciliate margins. 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Bertolonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="16" pageNumber="169" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="igrapiuna">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="169">Bertolonia igrapiuna</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs by the leaf blades only glandulose-punctate (
<emphasis box="[843,866,483,508]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="169">vs</emphasis>
. the abaxial surface also sparsely glandulose-pilose in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="De Candolle" authorityYear="1828" baseAuthorityName="Bonpland" baseAuthorityYear="1823" box="[165,297,518,544]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Bertolonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="16" pageNumber="169" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="leuzeana">
<emphasis box="[165,297,518,544]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="169">B. leuzeana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), petals with apiculate apex ending in a glandular head (
<emphasis box="[936,959,519,544]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="169">vs</emphasis>
. petals not apiculate) and anthers dehiscing through an extrorse pore (
<emphasis box="[427,450,555,580]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="169">vs</emphasis>
. introrse pore). For more details see 
<bibRefCitation author="Bisewski, G. C. A. &amp; Bacci, L. &amp; Amorim, A. M. A. &amp; Goldenberg, R." box="[863,1111,554,580]" pageId="16" pageNumber="169" pagination="563 - 574" refId="ref18940" refString="Bisewski, G. C. A., Bacci, L. F, Amorim, A. M. A. &amp; Goldenberg, R. (2020) Novelties in Bertolonia (Melastomataceae) from northeastern Brazil. Brazilian Journal of Botany 43 (3): 563 - 574. https: // doi. org / 10.1007 / s 40415 - 020 - 00630 - 7" type="journal article" year="2020">
Bisewski 
<emphasis box="[973,1029,554,580]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="169">et al.</emphasis>
(2020)
</bibRefCitation>
and 
<tableCitation box="[1164,1248,554,580]" captionStart="TABLE 1" captionStartId="6.[136,224,623,649]" captionText="TABLE 1. Selected morphological characters scored for species in Bertolonia that occur in the state of Bahia, Brazil. “GP”= Glandulose-punctate; “GV”= Glandulose-villose." pageId="16" pageNumber="169">Table 1</tableCitation>
.
</paragraph>
